<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-02 12:40:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Reds' Cameron Injured, Leaves Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Cincinnati Reds center fielder Mike Cameron  
left Saturday's game against the Milwaukee Brewers in the fourth 
inning with a strained left hamstring. 
</P>
<P>
	Cameron was playing center field when he fell to the grass for  
no apparent reason shortly after Milwaukee's Mark Loretta flied out 
to right. 
</P>
<P>
	He had difficulty standing up and had to be helped from the  
field by teammates and trainers. The Brewers led Cincinnati 7-4 at 
the time. 
</P>
<P>
	Cameron, who was 1-for-2 with an RBI single in the game, was  
replaced by Michael Tucker. Cameron, the Reds' leadoff hitter, is 
batting .256 with 21 homers and 66 RBIs. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
