</P>
<P>
	PHOENIX (AP) -- The only woman on death row in Arizona plans to  
marry a former German neo-Nazi convicted in the 1992 fire bombing 
of a Berlin cafe. Officials with the Arizona Department of 
Corrections said a German national named Ingo Hasselbach had 
proposed to Debra Milke in a letter. The two have never met or even 
spoken by phone. 

</P>
