</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Mets shut out the Pittsburgh  
Pirates 7-0 tonight to tie Cincinnati for the NL wild-card lead. 
Rick Reed pitched a three-hitter, struck out a career-high 12 and 
hit a two-run single, while Mike Piazza hit his 40th homer for the 
Mets. 

</P>
