</P>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Fredrik Modin scored the eventual game-winner  
with 2:01 remaining as the Tampa Bay Lightning won in Steve 
Ludzik's NHL coaching debut tonight, 4-2 over the New York 
Islanders. Modin, acquired from Toronto yesterday, scored from the 
left circle after Steve Guolla won a faceoff. Mike Sillinger added 
an empty net goal with 11 seconds left. 

</P>
