<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Trotting Triple Crown Winner Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HANOVER, Pa. (AP) -- Super Bowl, the most recent and only living  
winner of the Trotting Triple Crown, died Saturday from 
complications of old age at Hanover Shoe Farm. He was 30. 
</P>
<P>
	Super Bowl won the Trotting Triple Crown in 1972, including the  
prestigious Hambletonian. He had 38 wins in 51 lifetime starts with 
winnings of $600,156. 
</P>
<P>
	He was trained and driven by Stanley Dancer and owned during his  
racing career by Dancer's wife Rachel and Rose Hild Farm. 
</P>
<P>
	Starting in 1973, Super Bowl sired more than 1,400 racehorses  
who won $75.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Four of his sons, Speed Bowl (1982), Probe (1989), American  
Winner (1993) and Tagliabue (1995) also won the Hambletonian. 
</P>
<P>
	Super Bowl was a favorite with visitors to Hanover Shoe Farm  
because of his gregarious personality and appetite for food treats 
of any kind. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
