<HEADLINE> Ex-UK Starter Injured in Ohio </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Former University of Kentucky football  
player Jeremy Streck was in critical condition Saturday after being 
hit by a man who was charged with driving under the influence. 
</P>
<P>
	The 23-year-old Streck was hit at 3:10 a.m. EDT Friday in  
Columbus and taken to the Ohio State Medical Center. The family 
asked that no information other than his condition be released. 
</P>
<P>
	Police said Paul K. Synadinos, 20, of Gahanna, Ohio, was charged  
with DUI. 
</P>
<P>
	Streck was a starting senior offensive guard on the Kentucky  
team last season. 
</P>
<P>
	The wife of Streck's former high school coach in Cincinnati  
confirmed that Streck had received serious injuries in the 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've been told it's very serious,'' said Crystal Suriano,  
whose husband, Vince, coached Streck at Anderson High School. 
</P>
<P>
	``Jeremy was still friends with several of the players he played  
with here,'' Suriano said. ``Some of them have gone up to Columbus 
to see about him. We're all just beside ourselves.'' 
</P>
<P>
	UK football spokesman Tony Neely said Friday night that Kentucky  
coach Hal Mumme and his coaching staff had been made aware of the 
accident. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're extremely concerned for Jeremy and his family,'' Neely  
said. ``We'll be watching that situation and will be keeping Jeremy 
and his family in our thoughts and prayers.'' 
</P>
<P>
	A 6-foot-5, 313-pound lineman from Cincinnati, Streck started 18  
games and played in 32 during his Kentucky career. He started all 
12 games last season at left guard as the Wildcats went 7-5, making 
their first appearance in a New Year's Day bowl game since 1952. 
Streck also made the SEC Academic Honor roll last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Redshirted in 1994, Streck played defensive tackle as a redshirt  
freshman, totaling two tackles, one against Cincinnati and one 
versus Tennessee. 
</P>
<P>
	He moved to offensive line in 1995 and started seven games  
despite missing three games with a dislocated kneecap. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1997, as a junior, Streck alternated with Mike Webster at  
left guard. Last year, he took over the starting spot at left 
guard, while Webster moved over to right guard. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
