<HEADLINE> Predators Sign Forward Jason Dawe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- The Nashville Predators bolstered their  
offense on Saturday by signing free agent forward Jason Dawe. 
</P>
<P>
	Dawe, 26, has scored 20 or more goals three times in the NHL,  
most recently in the 1997-98 season when he had 20 with Buffalo and 
the New York Islanders. Terms of the deal were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
	The 5-foot-10, 190-pound right wing has played in 362 career  
games with the Sabres, Islanders and Montreal. He had only six 
goals last season with New York and Montreal. 
</P>
<P>
	He went to training camp with Edmonton, and Nashville general  
manager David Poile said Dawe was looking for a home and took a 
``hefty cut in pay.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``He's always been a goal scorer his whole career. We've got to  
find a way to get scoring chances,'' Poile said of a team that 
averaged 2.32 goals last season. 
</P>
<P>
	Dawe still has to clear waivers, but will be assigned to  
Nashville's IHL affiliate, the Milwaukee Admirals. 
</P>
<P>
	``Basically, show us your stuff and get back to where you were  
two years ago. There should be a good chance for you to get an 
opportunity here,'' Poile said he told Dawe. 
  	   	
</P>
