<HEADLINE> Sharp Appeal Wins in Miami Mile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- Sharp Appeal rallied to win the $255,000 Miami Mile  
Breeders' Cup Handicap on the grass at Calder Race Course on 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Javier Castellano, Sharp Appeal caught Shamrock City --  
a 13-1 shot -- to win by 1 3/4 lengths. Shamrock City held on for 
second by a length over Hurrahy. 
</P>
<P>
	Sharp Appeal ran the mile in 1:35.60, and the entry of the  
first- and third-place finishers paid $6.20, $3.40 and $3.40. 
Shamrock City paid $14 and $11. Unite's Big Red, the 8-5 favorite 
in the 11-horse field, was last on the backstretch and finished 
seventh. 
</P>
<P>
	On the first turn, Shamrock City, running on the inside, was  
head and head for the lead with Wertz. Sharp Appeal was seventh and 
Hurrahy was last. Unite's Big Red was ninth and dropped back 
entering the backstretch. 
</P>
<P>
	On the far turn, Shamrock City and Wertz remained even, a length  
in front of Tekken. Sharp Appeal moved into fifth on the outside. 
</P>
<P>
	Shamrock City shook off Wertz on the last turn, but Sharp Appeal  
caught him in midstretch and won going away. Hurrahy made up 
considerable ground in the drive to finish third. 
</P>
<P>
	Sharp Appeal, a 6-year-old, Florida-bred son of World Appeal,  
failed to win in seven previous starts this year, but had finished 
in the money in three graded stakes. Last year, he won the Grade 
III Bougainvillea Handicap at Hialeah. 
</P>
<P>
	Owned by Martin Cherry and trained by Marty Wolfson, Sharp  
Appeal has won 10 of 36 starts, has been in the money 25 times and 
has earned $686,621. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
