<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Khumba Mela Wins at Belmont </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Khumba Mela, an Irish-bred, turned what had been  
a closely contested race into a rout with a strong stretch run 
Saturday to win the $112,900, Grade III Noble Damsel Handicap at 
Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner reached the wire five lengths ahead of Uanme who was  
a neck ahead of Cyrillic in the field of eight fillies and mares 3 
years old and up. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Jose Santos and carrying 118 pounds, Khumba Mela  
covered one mile in 1:34:2 on a firm turf course and earned $67,740 
for Haras du Mezeray. It was the second win in five starts this 
year for the 4-year-old filly by Hero's Honor. 
</P>
<P>
	It was also the second lifetime graded stakes win for Khumba  
Mela who took Chantilly's Grade III Prix Chloe on July 17, 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	Khumba Mela returned $5.60, $3.20 and $2.50 as the second choice  
in the betting. Uanme paid $11 and $5.40, while Cyrillic was $3.40 
to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Chasin' Wimmin came from off the pace to provide an upset in the  
co-featured $57,600 Ashley T. Cole Handicap for 3-year-olds. The 
4-year-old gelding by Belong to Me carried 113 pounds and Jean-Luc 
Samyn over one mile in 1:34:4 on the turf. Pebo's Guy was runner-up 
in the 11-horse field, another three-quarters of a length before 
Currency Arbitrage. 
</P>
<P>
	Chasin' Wimmin returned $58 and earned $34,560 for Seymour Cohn  
with his first win in four starts this year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
