<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Magic Waives Forward Harvey Grant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- The Orlando Magic waived forward Harvey  
Grant on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Grant averaged 3.1 points and 2.3 rebounds last season for the  
Philadelphia 76ers. He was traded to Orlando in a three-player deal 
that sent Billy Owens to Philadelphia for Grant and Anthony Parker 
on Aug. 13. 
</P>
<P>
	Grant, a first-round pick by Washington in the 1988 NBA Draft,  
is averaging 9.9 points and 4.4 rebounds during his career. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
